{
  "stem": "13469.6",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We I've heard since, and maybe at that time, there were rumors, that we were going to Theresienstadt, which was sort of supposed to be a model camp, a relatively good camp, by comparison, and sort of centrally situated between the Russians and the Americans, so one that would stay in German hands probably the longest.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So maybe we did know that we were aiming for that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we certainly didn't go in that direction, because we started off going north.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And Theresienstadt was going south, almost.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we left Belsen on the 10th of April.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Who's we?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Rudi and me.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were all on this train, which turned out to be the third train, which turned out to have also the Birnbaums and the orphanage with all their people.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Basically, as far as we know, it was all the people from the star camp, about 2,000, 2,500 people. 2,500 people, maybe, that was left from the star camp all went onto this train.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We know that there were two other trains.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We believe one of them were a lot of Hungarians who were also destined for some kind of exchange, which Eichmann a long time previously tried to arrange-- Jews for trucks or Jews for money kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And these Hungarians, about 2,000 of them, were in another section of Belsen not far from us.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they apparently all went on one of these trains.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then other people went on one of the other trains.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But we missed the best part of Belsen, really, which was the liberation, which happened on the 15th, five days after we left Belsen.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
